pageContext.claim: “You probably saw last night I was in Florida and we had 9,000 seats in the auditorium. That was packed, and we had thousands outside and in these rooms all over the place. I guess they had at least 15,000, 18,000 people that couldn't get in last night -- which I hate. So we're actually starting to put up big screens.”
pageContext.analysis: The Tampa Bay Times reported that the crowd in the auditorium numbered nearly 10,000 for this Trump rally, but that there were only “hundreds” of people outside the venue and no big TV screens.
